Verified March 2026: the product of the two states is asymptotically complementary:

**Vk × Ok → (1/2) × 2 = 1    as k → ∞**

Important precision: this is an **asymptotic claim**, not a finite identity. Vk × Ok approaches 1 but does not equal 1 at any finite k. This is the intended behavior — the system never resolves.

